GAME SIMULATION ENGINE (simulateGame.js)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Per-game outputs:
  - Home score, away score
  - Quarter-by-quarter score breakdown (distributeToQuarters)
  - Weather condition for the game
  - Full player stat lines for both teams

Player stat generation covers:
  - QB: completions, attempts, passing yards, TDs, interceptions
  - RB: carries, rushing yards, rushing TDs
  - WR/TE: targets, receptions, receiving yards, receiving TDs
  - DL/LB: tackles, sacks, TFL
  - DB: tackles, interceptions, pass deflections

Weather system (getWeather / weatherMultipliers):
  - Conditions: clear, rain, snow, wind
  - Week-aware (heavier weather more likely in late season weeks)
  - Each condition applies pass multiplier, rush multiplier, score multiplier

Home field advantage:
  - Home team scoring boost applied to final score
  - Away QB accuracy penalty (crowd noise simulation)

Depth chart integration:
  - getHealthyByGroup pulls active, non-injured players by position group
  - Cascades to WR2/RB2 automatically when WR1/RB1 are injured
  - Targets distributed proportionally down the depth chart

Stat distributions:
  - randomNormal function for realistic bell-curve stat generation
  - Team offense/defense ratings (getTeamRatings) influence output
  - Player individual attributes (attr) pulled from DB per player


PLAYER LIFECYCLE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Contracts:
  - Each player has salary (AAV), years remaining, signing bonus / dead cap
  - Salary cap enforced on signings, extensions, and restructures
  - Dead cap tracked on release

Injuries:
  - Random in-game injuries during simulation
  - Injured players marked inactive on roster
  - Practice squad auto-callup covers injured starters

Waiver Wire:
  - Released players placed on waivers with team + week stamp
  - CPU teams claim based on roster need + worst record priority
  - Unclaimed players revert to free agency

Player Progression / Regression (runs at season advance):
  - Dev trait determines improvement ceiling
  - Age brackets determine regression risk (decline after ~30)
  - Breakout bonuses for standout season performances
  - Applies across all key positional attributes

Retirement:
  - Aging veterans retire at end of season based on age + OVR thresholds
  - Retired players stored with final career stats

Hall of Fame Induction:
  - Retired players checked against career milestone thresholds
  - Qualifying players automatically inducted into hall_of_fame table
  - Viewable in Records → Hall of Fame tab


